@startuml Sequence_ActionApproval
title Feature 09 - Action Approval Flow

actor User
participant "Browser\n(ActionItem)" as UI
participant "React Query\nCache" as RQ
participant "tRPC API" as API
participant "BullMQ" as Queue
database "PostgreSQL" as DB
participant "SSE\nEndpoint" as SSE

User -> UI : Tap "Approve" button

UI -> RQ : Optimistic update:\nremove from pending,\nadd to inProgress
RQ --> UI : Re-render immediately\n(action moves to In Progress tab)

UI -> API : action.approve({ actionId })
API -> DB : UPDATE actions\nSET status='approved',\napproved_at=now()
API -> Queue : Enqueue job:\naction.execute({ actionId })
API --> UI : { success: true }

note right of RQ
    If mutation fails,
    React Query rolls back
    the optimistic update.
end note

Queue -> Queue : Worker picks up job\n(cancellation/negotiation)

Queue -> DB : UPDATE actions\nSET status='in_progress'
Queue -> SSE : Publish to Redis\nuser:{id}:actions

SSE --> UI : SSE event:\n{ type: 'action.status_changed',\n  actionId, status: 'in_progress' }

UI -> RQ : invalidateQueries(['actions'])
RQ -> API : action.list() (refetch)
API --> RQ : Updated action list

note right of Queue
    Worker continues executing
    the action (call provider,
    navigate portal, etc.)
end note

Queue -> DB : UPDATE actions\nSET status='completed'
Queue -> SSE : Publish status change

SSE --> UI : SSE event:\n{ status: 'completed',\n  savings: 127.00 }
UI -> RQ : invalidateQueries(['actions',\n'dashboard', 'savings'])

@enduml
